    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/306</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-10T18:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11:20 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>My colleague at The Hague informs me that memorandum referred to in my August 9,
                    6 [1] a.m. was authentic.<note n="1" xml:id="d121fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>
                        <ref target="#pg_51">p. 51</ref>
                    </note> I learn quite confidentially from the Foreign Office, however, that text
                    has been presented to the Belgian Government by an individual requested to do so
                    by the Netherlands Government. Answer indignantly rejecting it is now being
                        prepared.<note n="2" xml:id="d121fn2">see the Belgian Minister’s note of
                        September 5, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_97"
                            >pp.97</ref>–<ref target="#pg_98">8</ref>
                    </note> We are thus spared further embarrassment and the subject is disposed of
                    so far as we are concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
